full_text: A location group is a collection of locations that link to different pages. AccountFile.PCF is a location group for the accounts. Some key properties include CanVisit, Menu Actions. The Info Bar and Tab Bar are also defined on the Properties tab. The Variables are on the Variables tab. The Entry Points tab displays entry points to the PCF file. Click on the Account File entry point to display its signature. Entry Points define the signature used by other widgets to navigate to the Location Group. The Location Group PCF file contains a list of location refs, which link to pages or child location groups. Let us select the Location Ref for Account File Summary. Control-click the Location link to navigate to the referenced PCF file. This opens the Account File Summary page PCF file. Open the Team Location Group. The CanVisit property of a Location Group controls whether the link to the Location Group is visible. The Team Location Group is a good example. The CanVisit field evaluates the View Team permission of a user. Log in as Alice Applegate. The Team tab is not visible because Alice does not have permission to view the team. Next, log in as Supervisor Steve Smith. The Team tab is now visible because the user does have permission to view the team. In Studio, open the tab bar.pcf file. The Search tab is a simple example to show how to navigate from a widget to a Location Group. The Action property of the Search tab is set to the entry point of the Search Location Group. Control-click the Action link Search to visit the PCF file. It opens the Location Group, Search.pcf. Go to the Entry Point properties of the Search Location Group. Click on the Entry Point to view its signature. Verify that the Entry Point signature matches that of the Action property on the Search tab. This ends the overview for Location Group's demonstration. segments.text: A location group is a collection of locations that link to different pages. AccountFile.PCF is a location group for the accounts.
Some key properties include CanVisit, Menu Actions. The Info Bar and Tab Bar are also defined on the Properties tab. The Variables are on the Variables tab.
The Entry Points tab displays entry points to the PCF file. Click on the Account File entry point to display its signature.
Entry Points define the signature used by other widgets to navigate to the Location Group.
The Location Group PCF file contains a list of location refs, which link to pages or child location groups.
Let us select the Location Ref for Account File Summary.
Control-click the Location link to navigate to the referenced PCF file.
This opens the Account File Summary page PCF file.
Open the Team Location Group.
The CanVisit property of a Location Group controls whether the link to the Location Group is visible.
The Team Location Group is a good example.
The CanVisit field evaluates the View Team permission of a user.
Log in as Alice Applegate.
The Team tab is not visible because Alice does not have permission to view the team.
Next, log in as Supervisor Steve Smith.
The Team tab is now visible because the user does have permission to view the team.
In Studio, open the tab bar.pcf file.
The Search tab is a simple example to show how to navigate from a widget to a Location Group.
The Action property of the Search tab is set to the entry point of the Search Location Group.
Control-click the Action link Search to visit the PCF file.
It opens the Location Group, Search.pcf.
Go to the Entry Point properties of the Search Location Group.
Click on the Entry Point to view its signature.
Verify that the Entry Point signature matches that of the Action property on the Search tab.
This ends the overview for Location Group's demonstration.
